meta {
  name: POST charging actions update-settings (v2.10.0)
  type: http
  seq: 47
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/charging/actions/update-settings
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "targetSoc_pct": 80,
    "maxChargeCurrentAC": "MAXIMUM",
    "autoUnlockPlugWhenCharged": "PERMANENT"
  }
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 - update charge plan settings via the dedicated action
  endpoint instead of the legacy /charging/settings PUT route. Exposed
  in HA as the `vag_connect.update_charging_settings` service.

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection.

  All body fields are optional. Backend keeps existing values for
  fields the caller omits. Known shape variants observed across
  firmware: targetSoc_pct vs targetSocPct vs
  targetStateOfChargeInPercent; maxChargeCurrentAC vs maxAcAmpere.

  Response: 204 No Content on success, or 400 with a per-field error
  list when validation fails (e.g. targetSoc below the brand's
  minimum, currently 50%).
}
